WEBVTT

00:12.664 --> 00:15.406
Narrator: AT THIS VERY MOMENT
IN THE TOWN OF COEUR d'COEURS,

00:15.450 --> 00:18.235
YOUNG NED WAS 9 YEARS,
27 WEEKS,

00:18.279 --> 00:20.629
6 DAYS, AND 3 MINUTES OLD.

00:26.591 --> 00:29.029
HIS DOG, DIGBY,
WAS 3 YEARS, 2 WEEKS,

00:29.072 --> 00:31.944
6 DAYS, 5 HOURS,
AND 9 MINUTES OLD...

00:35.731 --> 00:37.602
...AND NOT A MINUTE OLDER.

00:37.646 --> 00:39.082
[ HORN HONKS ]

00:39.126 --> 00:40.518
[ BARKS ]

01:18.165 --> 01:19.731
[ BARKS ]

01:19.775 --> 01:21.994
THIS WAS THE MOMENT
YOUNG NED REALIZED

01:22.038 --> 01:24.084
HE WASN'T LIKE
THE OTHER CHILDREN,

01:24.127 --> 01:27.739
NOR WAS HE LIKE ANYONE ELSE,
FOR THAT MATTER.

01:27.783 --> 01:29.872
YOUNG NED COULD TOUCH
DEAD THINGS

01:29.915 --> 01:32.744
AND BRING THEM BACK TO LIFE.

01:32.788 --> 01:34.398
[ CHATTERS ]

01:44.104 --> 01:46.367
THIS TOUCH WAS A GIFT
GIVEN TO HIM,

01:46.410 --> 01:48.369
BUT NOT BY ANYONE IN PARTICULAR.

01:53.983 --> 01:56.159
THERE WAS NO BOX,
NO INSTRUCTIONS,

01:56.203 --> 01:59.119
NO MANUFACTURER'S WARRANTY.

01:59.162 --> 02:01.033
IT JUST WAS.

02:01.077 --> 02:02.470
[ BUZZES ]

02:02.513 --> 02:04.994
THE TERMS OF USE
WEREN'T IMMEDIATELY CLEAR,

02:05.037 --> 02:07.997
NOR WERE THEY
OF IMMEDIATE CONCERN.

02:08.040 --> 02:09.912
YOUNG NED WAS IN LOVE.

02:09.955 --> 02:11.522
HER NAME WAS CHUCK.

02:11.566 --> 02:14.395
AT THIS VERY MOMENT,
SHE WAS 8 YEARS, 42 WEEKS,

02:14.438 --> 02:16.919
3 HOURS, AND 2 MINUTES OLD.

02:16.962 --> 02:19.313
YOUNG NED DID NOT THINK OF HER
AS BEING BORN

02:19.356 --> 02:21.619
OR HATCHED
OR CONCEIVED IN ANY WAY.

02:21.663 --> 02:23.099
CHUCK CAME READY-MADE

02:23.143 --> 02:26.668
FROM THE PLAY-DOH FUN FACTORY
OF LIFE.

02:26.711 --> 02:28.278
IN THEIR IMAGINATIONS,

02:28.322 --> 02:31.847
YOUNG NED AND A GIRL NAMED CHUCK
CONQUERED THE WORLD.

02:31.890 --> 02:33.370
AAH!

02:33.414 --> 02:34.458
AAH!

02:34.502 --> 02:36.765
[ SCREAMING ]

02:36.808 --> 02:37.983
[ WHIMPERS ]

02:48.864 --> 02:50.909
LONG AFTER THEIR PLAYDATE
WAS OVER,

02:50.953 --> 02:55.175
YOUNG NED REMAINED
UNDER CHUCK'S SPELL...

02:55.218 --> 02:57.873
UNTIL A BLOOD VESSEL
IN HIS MOTHER'S BRAIN BURST,

02:57.916 --> 03:00.397
KILLING HER INSTANTLY.

03:20.112 --> 03:22.637
MUST HAVE SLIPPED.
CLUMSY.

03:22.680 --> 03:25.248
DID THE TIMER GO OFF?

03:31.298 --> 03:35.563
YOUNG NED'S RANDOM GIFT THAT WAS
CAME WITH A CAVEAT OR TWO.

03:41.786 --> 03:44.180
IT WAS A GIFT
THAT NOT ONLY GAVE.

03:44.224 --> 03:45.268
[ DINGS ]

03:45.312 --> 03:47.009
IT TOOK.

03:47.052 --> 03:50.273
YOUNG NED DISCOVERED HE COULD
ONLY BRING THE DEAD BACK TO LIFE

03:50.317 --> 03:53.798
FOR ONE MINUTE
WITHOUT CONSEQUENCE.

03:53.842 --> 03:58.238
ANY LONGER,
AND SOMEONE ELSE HAD TO DIE.

03:58.281 --> 04:00.631
IN THE GRAND UNIVERSAL SCHEME
OF THINGS,

04:00.675 --> 04:02.851
YOUNG NED HAD TRADED
HIS MOTHER'S LIFE

04:02.894 --> 04:04.548
FOR CHUCK'S FATHER'S.

04:04.592 --> 04:06.246
COME ON, BIG DADDY,
INTO BED.

04:06.289 --> 04:08.857
BUT THERE WAS ONE MORE THING
ABOUT TOUCHING DEAD THINGS

04:08.900 --> 04:10.728
THAT YOUNG NED DIDN'T KNOW,

04:10.772 --> 04:14.166
AND HE LEARNED IT
IN THE MOST UNFORTUNATE WAY.

04:30.226 --> 04:32.446
FIRST TOUCH -- LIFE.

04:32.489 --> 04:36.450
SECOND TOUCH --
DEAD AGAIN FOREVER.

04:38.669 --> 04:42.151
HE MAKETH ME TO LIE DOWN
IN GREEN PASTURES.

04:42.194 --> 04:43.761
HE LEADETH ME BESIDE...

04:43.805 --> 04:45.850
Narrator:
AFTER A BRIEF MOURNING PERIOD,

04:45.894 --> 04:48.766
YOUNG NED'S FATHER WOULD HUSTLE
HIM OFF TO BOARDING SCHOOL,

04:48.810 --> 04:51.813
NEVER TO BE SEEN AGAIN.

04:51.856 --> 04:54.816
CHUCK WOULD BE FOSTERED
BY AUNTS LILY AND VIVIAN.

04:54.859 --> 04:56.948
A RENOWNED
SYNCHRONIZED-SWIMMING DUO,

04:56.992 --> 04:59.560
THEY SHARED MATCHING
PERSONALITY DISORDERS

04:59.603 --> 05:02.302
AND A LOVE FOR FINE CHEESE.

05:08.612 --> 05:10.919
AT THEIR RESPECTIVE PARENTS'
FUNERALS,

05:10.962 --> 05:14.705
DIZZY WITH GRIEF, CURIOSITY,
AND HORMONES,

05:14.749 --> 05:20.407
YOUNG NED AND A GIRL NAMED CHUCK
HAD THEIR FIRST AND ONLY KISS.

05:23.279 --> 05:26.804
AFTER HIS MOTHER'S DEATH,
NED AVOIDED SOCIAL ATTACHMENTS,

05:26.848 --> 05:30.068
FEARING WHAT HE'D DO
IF SOMEONE ELSE HE LOVED DIED.

05:31.679 --> 05:35.160
AND HE BECAME OBSESSED
WITH PIES.

05:35.204 --> 05:39.774
IT'S 19 YEARS, 34 WEEKS,
1 DAY, AND 59 MINUTES LATER,

05:39.817 --> 05:43.430
HERETOFORE KNOWN AS NOW.

05:43.473 --> 05:46.998
YOUNG NED HAS BECOME
THE PIE MAKER.

05:49.697 --> 05:52.395
AND THIS IS WHERE HE MAKES
HIS PIES.

05:52.439 --> 05:53.788
THE PEACHES NEVER BROWN.

05:53.831 --> 05:55.790
THE DEAD FRUIT IN HIS HANDS

05:55.833 --> 05:58.793
BECOMES RIPE
WITH EVERLASTING FLAVOR,

05:58.836 --> 06:03.232
AS LONG AS HE ONLY
TOUCHES IT ONCE.

06:03.275 --> 06:04.973
EVERY DAY I COME IN,
I PICK A PIE.

06:05.016 --> 06:07.410
I CONCENTRATE ALL MY LOVE
ON THAT PIE,

06:07.454 --> 06:09.325
'CAUSE IF I LOVE IT,
SOMEONE ELSE IS GONNA LOVE IT.

06:09.369 --> 06:10.935
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:10.979 --> 06:12.459
BY THE END OF THE DAY,
I'VE SOLD MORE OF THOSE PIES

06:12.502 --> 06:14.852
THAN ANY OTHER PIE
IN THE BAKERY.

06:14.896 --> 06:17.812
WHAT PIE
DO YOU LOVE TODAY?
RHUBARB.

06:17.855 --> 06:20.641
I'LL STICK WITH THREE-PLUM,
A LA MODE.

06:21.816 --> 06:23.818
HMM.

06:23.861 --> 06:27.430
EMERSON COD WAS THE SOLE KEEPER
OF THE PIE MAKER'S SECRET,

06:27.474 --> 06:28.997
AND THIS IS HOW HE CAME TO BE

06:29.040 --> 06:32.435
THE SOLE KEEPER
OF THE PIE MAKER'S SECRET.

06:32.479 --> 06:35.307
A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR,
MR. COD MET THE PIE MAKER

06:35.351 --> 06:38.049
WHEN HIS PIE HOLE WAS
ON THE VERGE OF FINANCIAL RUIN.

06:38.093 --> 06:40.574
[ GRUNTS ]

06:47.189 --> 06:48.277
WHOA.

06:48.320 --> 06:49.409
HEY!

06:51.193 --> 06:53.500
Narrator:
MR. COD PROPOSED A PARTNERSHIP.

06:53.543 --> 06:55.545
MURDERS ARE MUCH EASIER TO SOLVE

06:55.589 --> 06:58.200
WHEN YOU CAN ASK THE VICTIM
WHO KILLED THEM.

06:58.243 --> 07:00.898
THE PIE MAKER
RELUCTANTLY AGREED.

07:04.467 --> 07:06.469
Ned: I ASKED YOU NOT TO USE
THE WORD "ZOMBIE."

07:06.513 --> 07:08.950
IT'S DISRESPECTFUL. STUMBLING
AROUND, SQUAWKING FOR BRAINS --

07:08.993 --> 07:10.430
THAT'S NOT HOW THEY DO.

07:10.473 --> 07:12.388
AND UNDEAD?
NOBODY WANTS TO BE UN-ANYTHING.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.129
WHY BEGIN A STATEMENT
WITH A NEGATIVE?

07:14.172 --> 07:15.696
IT'S LIKE SAYING,
"I DON'T DISAGREE."

07:15.739 --> 07:17.175
JUST SAY YOU AGREE.

07:17.219 --> 07:18.699
ARE YOU COMFORTABLE
WITH "LIVING DEAD"?

07:18.742 --> 07:20.309
WHEN YOU'RE LIVING,
YOU'RE ALIVE.

07:20.352 --> 07:22.311
WHEN YOU'RE DEAD,
THAT'S WHAT YOU ARE.

07:22.354 --> 07:25.575
BUT WHEN YOU'RE DEAD THEN YOU'RE
NOT, YOU'RE ALIVE AGAIN.

07:25.619 --> 07:28.883
CAN'T WE SAY "ALIVE AGAIN"?
DOESN'T THAT SOUND NICE?

07:28.926 --> 07:30.711
SOUNDS LIKE
YOU'RE A NARCOLEPTIC.

07:30.754 --> 07:32.495
I SUFFER FROM SUDDEN
AND UNCONTROLLABLE ATTACKS

07:32.539 --> 07:33.801
OF DEEP SLEEP?

07:33.844 --> 07:36.412
WHAT'S THE OTHER ONE?NECROPHILIAC.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.936
WORDS THAT SOUND ALIKE
GET MIXED UP IN MY HEAD.

07:38.980 --> 07:42.462
ME TOO. I THOUGHT "MASTURBATION"
MEANT CHEWING YOUR FOOD.

07:44.725 --> 07:46.901
I DON'T THINK THAT ANYMORE.

07:46.944 --> 07:49.077
CAN YOU LOCK THE DOOR
BEHIND YOU?

07:55.039 --> 07:57.564
SO YOU WANT IN
ON THIS OPPORTUNITY OR NOT?

07:57.607 --> 07:59.000
A DOG IS INVOLVED.

07:59.043 --> 08:00.523
[ WHIMPERS ]

08:00.567 --> 08:03.091
-WHAT KIND OF DOG?
-IT'S GONNA BE A DEAD DOG.

08:03.134 --> 08:04.788
A DEAD DOG
NAMED CANTALOUPE.

08:04.832 --> 08:06.877
THEY'RE PUTTING HER DOWN.
ALLEGEDLY KILLED HER OWNER.

08:06.921 --> 08:08.139
WHEN YOU SAY
"ALLEGEDLY"...

08:08.183 --> 08:09.967
CANTALOUPE WAS FRAMED.

08:10.011 --> 08:11.708
SOMEONE PUT A PART
OF THE VICTIM IN HER MOUTH.HUH.

08:11.752 --> 08:13.884
HEY, DOCILE AS A KITTEN
SAYS THE FAMILY.

08:13.928 --> 08:15.364
DESPITE IT BEING A CHOW,

08:15.407 --> 08:17.366
THE BREED MOST LIKELY
TO TURN ON ITS OWNER?

08:17.409 --> 08:20.021
HEY, HEY.
THAT'S RACIAL PROFILING.

08:20.064 --> 08:21.979
IF THE DOG IS INNOCENT,
THEN IT'S MURDER,

08:22.023 --> 08:23.938
AND IF IT'S MURDER,
THEN THERE'S A REWARD.

08:23.981 --> 08:25.548
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

08:25.592 --> 08:28.725
ONE LEONARD GASWINT,
39 YEARS, 42 WEEKS,

08:28.769 --> 08:31.554
5 DAYS, 3 HOURS,
AND 26 MINUTES OLD,

08:31.598 --> 08:34.470
WAS FOUND MAULED TO DEATH
IN HIS HOME OFFICE.

08:34.514 --> 08:37.081
HIS DOG, CANTALOUPE,
WAS THE SOLE WITNESS

08:37.125 --> 08:39.214
AND ONLY SUSPECT IN THE MURDER.

08:39.257 --> 08:42.130
CONVINCED OF HER INNOCENCE,
THE GASWINT FAMILY OFFERED

08:42.173 --> 08:45.220
A SIGNIFICANT REWARD
TO FIND THE REAL KILLER.

08:45.263 --> 08:47.570
YOU THE DOG EXPERT?UH-HUH.

08:47.614 --> 08:49.354
ALREADY HAD A DOG EXPERT.

08:49.398 --> 08:51.748
I'M THE, UH, OTHER ONE.

08:51.792 --> 08:54.359
MM-HMM.

08:54.403 --> 08:55.752
HOW'S HE LOOK?

08:55.796 --> 08:57.580
FINE, BUT MY THRESHOLD'S
PRETTY HIGH,

08:57.624 --> 09:02.063
SO YOU HAVE TO TAKE WHAT I SAY
WITH A GRAIN OF SALT.

09:02.106 --> 09:03.804
THAT AIN'T
A GRAIN OF SALT.

09:03.847 --> 09:05.762
THAT'S ONE OF THEM BLOCKS
THEY GIVE COWS TO LICK.

09:05.806 --> 09:07.198
HE CAN'T HELP HOW HE IS.

09:07.242 --> 09:09.026
THAT DON'T MAKE IT
ANY LESS TRAUMATIC.

09:09.070 --> 09:10.288
FOR WHO?
ME.

09:10.332 --> 09:12.813
AND I'M SURE HIM,
BUT MAINLY ME.

09:12.856 --> 09:15.119
I'M GONNA WAIT OUTSIDE.

09:19.559 --> 09:21.256
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:21.299 --> 09:23.563
[ WATCH TICKING ]

09:27.175 --> 09:28.698
HELLO.
HI.

09:28.742 --> 09:31.179
UH, SORRY TO DISTURB YOU,
MR. GASWINT OR LEONARD.

09:31.222 --> 09:33.094
DO YOU PREFER --
LEO!

09:33.137 --> 09:37.315
LEO. UM,
YOUR CURRENT CONDITION --

09:37.359 --> 09:39.230
DO I HAVE SOMETHING
RIGHT HERE?

09:39.274 --> 09:40.536
NO.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.103
THERE'S NOTHING
RIGHT THERE.

09:42.146 --> 09:43.757
DAMN DOG.
CANTALOUPE?

09:43.800 --> 09:45.715
NO, NO.
CANTALOUPE'S DOCILE AS A KITTEN.

09:45.759 --> 09:47.325
IT'S THAT ROTTWEILER.

09:47.369 --> 09:49.110
MY SECRETARY SICCED HER DOG
ON ME.

09:49.153 --> 09:51.895
SHE'S BEEN UPSET SINCE
LAST YEAR'S CHRISTMAS PARTY.

09:51.939 --> 09:54.289
YOU KNOW,
IT'S A FUNNY STORY. I --

09:57.031 --> 09:58.989
WAS IT THE CHOW?

09:59.033 --> 10:01.731
THE SECRETARY
WITH HER ROTTWEILER.

10:06.431 --> 10:07.911
HMM.

10:11.480 --> 10:14.657
Narrator: HER GOOD NAME CLEARED
AND HER EXECUTION STAYED,

10:14.701 --> 10:16.528
CANTALOUPE WAS FREED,

10:16.572 --> 10:18.487
AND THE SECRETARY
AND HER ROTTWEILER

10:18.530 --> 10:20.141
WERE HAULED TO JUSTICE.

10:20.184 --> 10:22.317
Woman: AN ANONYMOUS TIP
LED TO SOLVING THE MURDER

10:22.360 --> 10:23.927
OF A MICHIGAN ENTREPRENEUR

10:23.971 --> 10:26.364
THOUGHT TO BE MAULED TO DEATH
BY A FAMILY PET.

10:26.408 --> 10:28.497
THE TRUTH, HOWEVER,
IS MUCH MORE SINISTER.

10:28.540 --> 10:31.761
OLIVE SNOOK ENJOYED
HER TIME WITH DIGBY.

10:31.805 --> 10:33.894
HE WAS A SURROGATE
FOR THE HUMAN CONNECTION

10:33.937 --> 10:35.504
SHE WANTED WITH THE PIE MAKER.

10:35.547 --> 10:37.158
HER DESPERATE ATTEMPTS

10:37.201 --> 10:39.639
TO CONNECT TO SOMEONE
SO DISCONNECTED TERRIFIED HIM.

10:39.682 --> 10:41.336
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

10:41.379 --> 10:43.077
BUT THAT DIDN'T STOP HER
FROM TRYING.

10:43.120 --> 10:44.600
HOW WAS YOUR CONVENTION?

10:44.644 --> 10:46.080
CONVENTIONAL.

10:46.123 --> 10:47.516
HOW WAS DIGBY?

10:47.559 --> 10:49.344
NEUROTIC.
HE'S A VERY NEEDY DOG.

10:49.387 --> 10:51.172
MAYBE IF YOU PET HIM
ONCE IN A WHILE,

10:51.215 --> 10:52.782
HE WOULDN'T BE
SO NEUROTIC.

10:52.826 --> 10:54.654
I'M ALLERGIC,
SO I CAN'T ACTUALLY TOUCH HIM,

10:54.697 --> 10:55.959
BUT I PET HIM.

10:56.003 --> 10:57.874
WITH A STICK?
HOW DO YOU PET HIM?

10:57.918 --> 10:59.876
A STICK IS INVOLVED,
BUT IT'S MORE LIKE A HANDLE

10:59.920 --> 11:01.356
TO A, UM, PET--
PETTING DEVICE.

11:01.399 --> 11:04.228
A DOG NEEDS TO BE
TOUCHED.

11:04.272 --> 11:07.101
WE ALL NEED TO BE TOUCHED.

11:07.144 --> 11:09.146
YOU TOUCH HIM.
OTHER PEOPLE TOUCH HIM.

11:09.190 --> 11:13.890
HE'S YOUR DOG.
DO YOU TOUCH ANYTHING?

11:13.934 --> 11:18.329
OF COURSE. I, UH...
I-I TOUCH LOTS OF THINGS.

11:18.373 --> 11:20.201
WITH AFFECTION?

11:20.244 --> 11:23.421
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME SOMEONE
TOUCHED YOU WITH AFFECTION?

11:25.380 --> 11:28.122
I GET TOUCHED.

11:28.165 --> 11:30.690
CAN YOU GET
DIGBY'S LEASH NOW?

11:33.997 --> 11:36.957
HMM.

11:37.000 --> 11:38.741
YOU DON'T MIND
THAT I DON'T TOUCH YOU, DO YOU?

11:38.785 --> 11:40.482
[ WHIMPERS ]

11:40.525 --> 11:43.267
Narrator: THEN CAME THE EVENT
THAT CHANGED EVERYTHING.

11:43.311 --> 11:44.878
THE BODY OF A YOUNG WOMAN

11:44.921 --> 11:46.618
ALLEGEDLY MURDERED
ABOARD A CRUISE SHIP

11:46.662 --> 11:48.229
HAS BEEN RECOVERED
FROM THE SEA.

11:48.272 --> 11:50.187
THE VICTIM'S IDENTITY
IS BEING WITHHELD.

11:50.231 --> 11:52.450
THE PIE MAKER LISTENED
INTENTLY TO THE NEWS,

11:52.494 --> 11:54.235
UNAWARE THAT HE STOPPED
BREATHING.

11:54.278 --> 11:56.106
HE WAS HAUNTED
BY THE NAMELESS WOMAN

11:56.150 --> 11:58.326
WHO MET HER END
ON THE HIGH SEAS.

11:58.369 --> 12:01.285
[ SIGHS ]
WELL, THERE'S YOUR LEASH.

12:01.329 --> 12:02.634
BUT HE DIDN'T KNOW WHY.

12:02.678 --> 12:04.288
HER NAME STILL WITHHELD,

12:04.332 --> 12:06.203
VERY LITTLE IS KNOWN
OF THE VICTIM,

12:06.247 --> 12:08.118
WHO WAS REPORTEDLY
TRAVELING ALONE

12:08.162 --> 12:10.077
WHEN MURDERED
ABOARD A PASSENGER SHIP

12:10.120 --> 12:12.166
THAT WAS RETURNING
FROM A TROPICAL CRUISE

12:12.209 --> 12:14.298
SAILING BETWEEN
THE UNITED STATES AND TAHITI.

12:14.342 --> 12:16.300
THE SHIP'S CAPTAIN

12:16.344 --> 12:17.911
INITIALLY DISMISSED THE DEATH
AS AN ACCIDENT,

12:17.954 --> 12:20.217
SUGGESTING THE VICTIM

12:20.261 --> 12:22.785
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ] LIKELY RETURNED
FROM A LATE NIGHT OUT...,

12:25.135 --> 12:26.920
BEEN WATCHING THE NEWS
LATELY?

12:26.963 --> 12:28.486
THERE DOESN'T SEEM LIKE
MUCH GOING ON IN THE WORLD

12:28.530 --> 12:30.401
BESIDES A DEAD GIRL
IN A BOAT.

12:30.445 --> 12:32.490
A LOT GOING ON
WITH THAT DEAD GIRL.

12:32.534 --> 12:33.578
THAT SO?
MM-HMM.

12:33.622 --> 12:35.450
$50,000 WORTH
OF "THAT SO."

12:35.493 --> 12:38.018
YOU INTERESTED
IN A CONVERSATION?I COULD BE PERSUADED.

12:38.061 --> 12:40.455
QUICK, 'CAUSE THE DEAD GIRL'S
ABOUT TO GO IN THE GROUND.

12:40.498 --> 12:42.674
THEY JUST PULLED HER
OUT OF THE WATER.

12:42.718 --> 12:44.154
JEWISH.

12:44.198 --> 12:45.982
CHRISTIANS LEAVE THEM
LAYING AROUND.

12:46.026 --> 12:47.767
JEWS GOT TO
GET THEM BURIED.

12:47.810 --> 12:49.986
WHERE WE GOING?COEUR d'COEURS.
YOU EVER BEEN THERE?

12:50.030 --> 12:52.293
I GREW UP THERE, SORT OF.

12:52.336 --> 12:54.512
THIS DEAD GIRL FROM COEUR
d'COEURS -- WHAT IS HER NAME?

12:54.556 --> 12:56.210
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

12:58.473 --> 13:00.605
TRICK OR TREAT!TRICK OR TREAT!

13:01.389 --> 13:02.956
CHUCK.

13:14.054 --> 13:16.447
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER
NEVER RETURNED TO COEUR d'COEURS

13:16.491 --> 13:18.536
AFTER BEING SENT AWAY TO SCHOOL,

13:18.580 --> 13:21.496
BUT HE THOUGHT OF CHUCK
EVERY DAY.

13:21.539 --> 13:23.628
YOU KNOW THIS GIRL?I KNOW OFHER.

13:23.672 --> 13:25.282
KNOW OF HER
IN THE BIBLICAL SENSE?

13:25.326 --> 13:26.980
I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF HER
SINCE I WAS 10.

13:27.023 --> 13:29.156
THINK OF HER A LOT
WHEN YOU WERE 10?

13:29.199 --> 13:32.333
DON'T REMEMBER ANYTHING
WHEN I WAS 10.

13:32.376 --> 13:34.422
THE PIE MAKER REMEMBERS
EVERYTHING.

13:35.989 --> 13:37.860
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

13:37.904 --> 13:40.080
CHARLOTTE CHARLES,
28 YEARS, 24 WEEKS,

13:40.123 --> 13:42.647
3 DAYS, 11 HOURS,
AND 51 MINUTES OLD,

13:42.691 --> 13:44.693
WAS FOUND FLOATING IN THE OCEAN

13:44.736 --> 13:47.000
MOMENTS AFTER HER BODY
WAS DISCARDED THERE.

13:51.831 --> 13:54.572
"DISCARDED BY WHOM?"
SEEMED TO BE A QUESTION

13:54.616 --> 13:57.271
ONLY CHARLOTTE CHARLES
COULD ANSWER.

14:03.320 --> 14:04.756
[ GRUNTS ]

14:07.281 --> 14:08.717
Narrator:
THE FUNERAL DIRECTOR,

14:08.760 --> 14:10.414
ALWAYS EAGER
TO SUPPLEMENT HIS INCOME...

14:10.458 --> 14:12.286
GENTLEMEN.

14:12.329 --> 14:14.636
...WAS MORE THAN HAPPY TO GRANT
THE DECEASED AN AUDIENCE.

14:19.249 --> 14:21.643
UM, I JUST WANT TO --
I WANT TO --

14:21.686 --> 14:23.340
CAN I DO THIS ONE ALONE,
ON ACCOUNT OF, YOU KNOW,

14:23.384 --> 14:25.647
THE WHOLE
HISTORICAL CONTEXT?

14:25.690 --> 14:28.650
YOU GOT SOMETHING PERSONAL
YOU NEED TO SAY?
NO.

14:28.693 --> 14:30.217
OKAY, MAYBE.

14:30.260 --> 14:32.697
BUT I HAVE NOTHING TO GAIN BUT
A SMALL AMOUNT OF CLOSURE.

14:32.741 --> 14:35.004
WHAT YOU GOT SO OPEN
THAT NEEDS CLOSING?

14:35.048 --> 14:37.920
I JUST WANT TO SAY
I'M SORRY FOR SOMETHING.

14:37.964 --> 14:39.704
ONE OF THOSE STUPID THINGS
KIDS DO

14:39.748 --> 14:41.489
THEY DON'T KNOW
THEY'RE DOING.

14:41.532 --> 14:42.925
YEAH. WELL, YOU ASK
WHO KILLED HER FIRST.

14:42.969 --> 14:44.535
OKAY.

14:44.579 --> 14:45.710
YOU ONLY GOT A MINUTE.
I KNOW.

14:45.754 --> 14:46.929
60 SECONDS.
I KNOW.

14:46.973 --> 14:48.061
ALRIGHT.

15:04.773 --> 15:06.906
ONLY PRINCE CHARMING COULD KNOW

15:06.949 --> 15:09.996
HOW THE PIE MAKER FELT
UPON LOOKING AT HER.

15:10.039 --> 15:14.130
GREAT THOUGHT WAS TAKEN
AS TO WHERE TO TOUCH HER.

15:14.174 --> 15:17.220
THE LIPS -- TOO FORWARD.

15:17.264 --> 15:19.744
THE CHEEK -- THE CHEEK.

15:22.704 --> 15:24.140
OH!

15:24.184 --> 15:26.316
OH!

15:26.360 --> 15:27.709
CHUCK, WAIT!
WHO ARE YOU?

15:27.752 --> 15:29.624
DO YOU REMEMBER
THE LITTLE BOY

15:29.667 --> 15:32.757
WHO LIVED NEXT DOOR TO YOU
WHEN YOUR DAD DIED?
NED?

15:32.801 --> 15:34.890
OH, MY GOD.
HEY, HOW ARE YOU?

15:34.934 --> 15:36.283
GOOD.
YOU LOOK GREAT.

15:36.326 --> 15:38.328
DO YOU KNOW WHAT'S HAPPENING
RIGHT NOW?

15:38.372 --> 15:39.939
I HAD THE STRANGEST DREAM

15:39.982 --> 15:41.766
I WAS BEING STRANGLED TO DEATH
WITH A PLASTIC SACK.

15:41.810 --> 15:43.246
YOU WERESTRANGLED TO DEATH
WITH A PLASTIC SACK.

15:43.290 --> 15:44.813
THAT'S PROBABLY
AN ODD THING TO HEAR,

15:44.856 --> 15:47.163
BUT I WASN'T QUITE SURE
HOW TO SUGARCOAT IT.

15:47.207 --> 15:49.252
OH. OH.

15:49.296 --> 15:50.862
YOU ONLY HAVE A MINUTE --
LESS.

15:50.906 --> 15:52.429
WHAT CAN I DO
IN LESS THAN A MINUTE?

15:52.473 --> 15:54.214
YOU COULD TELL ME
WHO KILLED YOU

15:54.257 --> 15:56.564
SO, YOU KNOW,
JUSTICE CAN BE SERVED.

15:56.607 --> 15:58.044
THAT'S REALLY SWEET,
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHO KILLED ME.

15:58.087 --> 16:01.003
I DROPPED MY ROOM KEY
IN THE ICE MAKER,

16:01.047 --> 16:02.874
AND AS I WAS THINKING,
"THAT WAS DUMB"...

16:02.918 --> 16:04.876
AS SHE WAS THINKING,
"THAT WAS DUMB,"

16:04.920 --> 16:07.227
CHUCK WAS STRANGLED TO DEATH
WITH A PLASTIC SACK.

16:07.270 --> 16:08.924
AND THEN
YOU TOUCHED MY CHEEK.

16:08.968 --> 16:11.013
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

16:11.057 --> 16:13.233
JUST A SECOND.IS MY TIME UP?

16:13.276 --> 16:15.017
I'M SORRY.

16:15.061 --> 16:17.367
WELL, THANKS
FOR CALLING ME "CHUCK."

16:17.411 --> 16:20.718
DO YOU KNOW NO ONE'S
CALLED ME "CHUCK" SINCE...

16:20.762 --> 16:22.242
SINCE YOU?

16:22.285 --> 16:25.071
I USED TO, WHEN I LIVED
NEXT DOOR TO YOU,

16:25.114 --> 16:28.726
I HAD A CRU-- I WAS IN --
YOU WERE MY FIRST KISS.

16:30.119 --> 16:32.121
YEAH?

16:32.165 --> 16:34.906
YOU WERE MY FIRST KISS,
TOO.

16:34.950 --> 16:36.821
YOU WANT TO BE
MY LAST KISS?

16:36.865 --> 16:39.520
FIRST AND LAST --
OR IS THAT WEIRD?

16:40.695 --> 16:42.610
THAT'S NOT WEIRD.

16:42.653 --> 16:44.916
IT'S MAGICAL.

16:44.960 --> 16:47.658
CHUCK'S MINUTE OF LIFE
WAS NEARLY OVER.

16:51.662 --> 16:55.362
THE PIE MAKER'S LIPS WENT
AS FAR AS THEY WOULD GO.

16:55.405 --> 16:58.539
HE COULDN'T WILL THEM
TO GO ANY FURTHER.

17:02.934 --> 17:05.937
AND, AS A CONSEQUENCE...

17:05.981 --> 17:08.940
THE FUNERAL DIRECTOR
WOULD GO NO FURTHER.

17:11.900 --> 17:13.206
[ THUD ]

17:18.124 --> 17:20.604
HEY, IF YOU DON'T WANT TO
KISS ME, IT'S OKAY.

17:20.648 --> 17:24.608
NO, I WANT TO. I DO.
I...

17:24.652 --> 17:28.438
WHAT IF YOU
DIDN'T HAVE TO BE DEAD?

17:28.482 --> 17:31.050
WELL,
THAT WOULD BE PREFERABLE.

17:32.573 --> 17:34.444
NOBODY CAN KNOW.

17:34.488 --> 17:36.055
HOP IN.

17:36.098 --> 17:39.884
I GOT TO THINK OF A WAY
TO GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

17:39.928 --> 17:43.453
CAN YOU LIE REALLY STILL
UNTIL I GET BACK?

17:43.497 --> 17:45.064
MM-HMM.

17:46.978 --> 17:48.676
DOESN'T KNOW --
DIDN'TKNOW.

17:48.719 --> 17:51.113
SO SOMEBODY JUST THREW
HER CARCASS OFF A BOAT AND --

17:51.157 --> 17:53.028
WHY ARE YOU SWEATING?IT'S WARM IN THERE.
WHAT?

17:53.072 --> 17:54.464
YOUR EYE'S TWITCHING.
MY EYE?

17:54.508 --> 17:56.684
YOUR EYE IS TWITCHING.

17:56.727 --> 17:59.034
WHEN PEOPLE AREN'T BEING HONEST,
THEIR EYE TWITCHES.

17:59.078 --> 18:01.254
RIGHT THERE,
LIKE YOURS DID JUST NOW.

18:01.297 --> 18:03.125
IT'S NERVES, AGGRAVATED
BY A STOMACH THING.

18:03.169 --> 18:05.693
IT'S LIKE ACID REFLUX,
BUT IN MY EYE.

18:05.736 --> 18:07.912
I THINK I'M GONNA STAY
FOR THE SERVICE.

18:07.956 --> 18:10.263
IS THAT SO?JUST FEELING NOSTALGIC.

18:10.306 --> 18:12.091
DO YOU REMEMBER HOW TO GET BACK
TO THE STATION?

18:12.134 --> 18:15.442
IT'S DOWN THE, UH...
I'LL CATCH A LATER BUS.

18:55.090 --> 18:56.961
Narrator:
LYING IN THE DARK,

18:57.005 --> 19:01.009
CHUCK CONSIDERED HOW SHE CAME
TO BE LYING IN THE DARK.

19:01.052 --> 19:05.883
SHE CONSIDERED THE LIFE THAT WAS
WITH AUNTS LILY AND VIVIAN.

19:05.927 --> 19:07.668
THEIR PERSONALITY DISORDERS

19:07.711 --> 19:11.715
BLOSSOMED INTO
INCAPACITATING SOCIAL PHOBIAS,

19:11.759 --> 19:16.329
WHICH MADE IT DIFFICULT
FOR THEM TO LEAVE THE HOUSE.

19:16.372 --> 19:20.202
WHICH IN TURN MADE IT DIFFICULT
FOR CHUCK TO LEAVE THEM.

19:20.246 --> 19:22.073
SHE SERVED HER COMMUNITY

19:22.117 --> 19:24.641
BY HARVESTING HONEY
FOR THE HOMELESS.

19:24.685 --> 19:27.514
SHE NEVER STRAYED FAR FROM HOME.

19:27.557 --> 19:29.733
SHE READ ABOUT PEOPLE
SHE COULD NEVER BE

19:29.777 --> 19:32.910
AND ADVENTURES
SHE WOULD NEVER HAVE.

19:32.954 --> 19:36.218
LIFE WAS GOOD ENOUGH
UNTIL ONE DAY IT WASN'T.

19:36.262 --> 19:37.828
CHUCK WANTED MORE,

19:37.872 --> 19:40.135
BUT AT BOUTIQUE TRAVEL
TRAVEL BOUTIQUE,

19:40.179 --> 19:44.139
SHE GOT MORE
THAN SHE'D BARGAINED FOR.

19:44.183 --> 19:47.360
HEY, I THINK SOMEBODY'S
TRUCK'S ON FIRE.

19:47.403 --> 19:49.362
OH, GEE.

19:54.193 --> 19:55.455
SORRY I'M LATE.

19:55.498 --> 19:56.934
Narrator:
ONLY SLEEPING BEAUTY

19:56.978 --> 19:59.285
COULD KNOW HOW SHE FELT
AT THIS MOMENT.

20:03.680 --> 20:05.291
I CAN'T EVEN HUG YOU?
WHAT IF YOU NEED A HUG?

20:05.334 --> 20:07.336
A HUG CAN TURN
YOUR DAY AROUND.

20:07.380 --> 20:09.773
I'M NOT A FAN OF THE HUG.THEN YOU HAVEN'T
BEEN HUGGED PROPERLY.

20:09.817 --> 20:12.602
IT'S LIKE AN EMOTIONAL HEIMLICH.
PUTTING THEIR ARMS AROUND YOU

20:12.646 --> 20:15.736
AND THEY GIVE YOU A SQUEEZE,
AND ALL YOUR FEAR AND ANXIETY

20:15.779 --> 20:17.259
COMES SHOOTING OUT OF YOUR MOUTH

20:17.303 --> 20:18.565
IN A BIG, WET WAD,
AND YOU CAN BREATHE AGAIN.

20:18.608 --> 20:20.306
THAT'S FINE
FOR SOMEONE ELSE TO DO

20:20.349 --> 20:22.264
IF I'M CHOKING ON SOMETHING
OTHER THAN EMOTION,

20:22.308 --> 20:23.526
BUT YOU CAN'T TOUCH ME.

20:23.570 --> 20:25.485
SO A KISS IS
OUT OF THE QUESTION?

20:28.314 --> 20:30.533
I'VE LOST
MY TRAIN OF THOUGHT.

20:33.493 --> 20:35.756
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
BEEN THINKING ABOUT THIS?

20:35.799 --> 20:37.801
LIKE THINKINGTHINKING?
IT WASN'T PREMEDITATED.

20:37.845 --> 20:41.196
I WASN'T LYING IN WAIT. MORE
LIKE I WAS MUSING ON THE IDEA.

20:41.240 --> 20:44.330
NOT, YOU KNOW, DWELLING. THERE
WERE TIMES I DID DWELL ON YOU --

20:44.373 --> 20:47.071
ABOUT YOU -- A LITTLE. BUT I
WASN'T SERIOUSLY CONSIDERING

20:47.115 --> 20:51.380
TILL THE EXACT MOMENT I DID IT
OR DIDN'T DO IT.

20:51.424 --> 20:53.774
I ALWAYS WONDERED
IF YOU'D COME BACK.

20:53.817 --> 20:55.297
I GUESS YOU CAME BACK
WHEN I NEEDED YOU MOST.

20:55.341 --> 20:57.517
WELL, THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN
BEFORE I WAS KILLED,

20:57.560 --> 20:59.954
BUT THIS WORKED OUT.

20:59.997 --> 21:01.825
YOU UNDERSTAND
YOU CAN'T GO BACK, RIGHT?

21:01.869 --> 21:03.392
YOU CAN'T SEE YOUR AUNTS.

21:03.436 --> 21:05.176
THEY'LL GO OFF THEIR ROCKERS
WITHOUT ME.

21:05.220 --> 21:07.527
THEY'RE SHUT-INS. IT'S NOT LIKE
THEY TALK TO ANYBODY.

21:07.570 --> 21:09.659
PEOPLE AREN'T USED TO
THIS SORT OF THING.

21:09.703 --> 21:11.748
ISSUES OF MORALITY,
HOW COME SHE'S NOT DEAD ANYMORE?

21:11.792 --> 21:13.533
IT'D BE A DISASTER.

21:13.576 --> 21:16.405
I SUPPOSE DYING'S AS GOOD AN
EXCUSE AS ANY TO START LIVING.

21:20.061 --> 21:22.237
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:24.500 --> 21:26.197
Ned: THIS IS DIGBY.

21:26.241 --> 21:28.069
WASN'T YOUR OLD DOG
NAMED DIGBY?

21:28.112 --> 21:30.376
THIS IS HIM.

21:30.419 --> 21:33.335
DID YOU --
AND NOW HE'S -- HE'S...

21:33.379 --> 21:34.902
YEAH.

21:34.945 --> 21:37.296
YOU SEEM TO DO THAT A LOT.
WHY DO YOU DO THAT A LOT?

21:37.339 --> 21:39.820
IT'S JUST
THE TWO OF YOU.

21:39.863 --> 21:42.301
I HATE TO BE A BAD HOST,

21:42.344 --> 21:43.998
BUT I'M SORT OF EXHAUSTED
FROM CHASING YOUR COFFIN.

21:44.041 --> 21:45.521
OH, YEAH.
OF COURSE.

21:45.565 --> 21:47.610
I'M GONNA SLEEP HERE.
YOU TAKE THE BED.

21:47.654 --> 21:49.960
I INSIST.

21:50.004 --> 21:52.746
MY EYES ARE ROLLING BACK
INTO MY HEAD.

21:54.574 --> 21:57.272
I'M LAYING DOWN NOW.

22:05.019 --> 22:08.588
I'D KISS YOU
IF IT WOULDN'T KILL ME.

22:08.631 --> 22:10.764
28-YEAR-OLD LONELY TOURIST
CHARLOTTE CHARLES

22:10.807 --> 22:12.679
WAS LAID TO REST EARLIER TODAY.

22:12.722 --> 22:15.508
SHE IS SURVIVED BY HER AUNTS,
VIVIAN AND LILY CHARLES.

22:15.551 --> 22:17.466
Narrator:
IN A STRANGE BED

22:17.510 --> 22:19.512
WATCHING HER OWN FUNERAL
ON THE EVENING NEWS,

22:19.555 --> 22:24.038
CHUCK WAS STRUCK BY THE
UNDIGNIFIED NATURE OF CELEBRITY.

22:24.081 --> 22:26.997
NO ONE WANTS TO BE FAMOUS
FOR THE WAY THEY DIE.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.912
BOUTIQUE TRAVEL
TRAVEL BOUTIQUE HAS OFFERED

22:28.956 --> 22:31.915
A $50,000 REWARD IN THE MURDER
OF CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

22:35.266 --> 22:38.139
Chuck: NED.

22:38.182 --> 22:40.707
HMM? MMM.

22:40.750 --> 22:43.971
WOULD I BE ALIVE RIGHT NOW
IF I KNEW WHO KILLED ME?

22:44.014 --> 22:45.755
OF COURSE.
DON'T BE SILLY.

22:45.799 --> 22:47.627
SOMETHING IN THE NEWS
ABOUT THE REWARD?

22:47.670 --> 22:49.629
YOU WANTED TO KNOW WHO KILLED ME
SO JUSTICE COULD BE SERVED.

22:49.672 --> 22:51.674
I DON'T THINK
JUSTICE WAS ON THE MENU --

22:51.718 --> 22:53.589
MAYBE AS A SIDE DISH,
BUT NOT AS AN ENTRéE.

22:53.633 --> 22:56.984
IT WAS DEFINITELY AN ENTRéE.
CAN WE DROP THE METAPHOR?

22:57.027 --> 22:58.855
I WOULDN'T HAVE KNOWN
YOU HAD DIED

22:58.899 --> 23:00.422
IF IT WEREN'T
FOR THE REWARD.

23:00.466 --> 23:02.293
WHEN WERE YOU
GONNA TELL ME?

23:02.337 --> 23:03.469
IN THE MORNING
OR WHEN IT CAME UP --

23:03.512 --> 23:04.644
WHICHEVER
DIDN'T COME FIRST.

23:04.687 --> 23:06.428
$50,000?
THAT MAKES A LOT OF PIE.

23:06.472 --> 23:08.299
$25,000.
I HAVE A BUSINESS PARTNER.

23:08.343 --> 23:10.954
IT'S A BUSINESS?
NOT IN
THE TRADITIONAL SENSE.

23:10.998 --> 23:13.174
YOU TOUCH MURDER VICTIMS,
YOU ASK WHO KILLED THEM,

23:13.217 --> 23:15.655
YOU TOUCH THEM AGAIN,
THEY GO BACK TO BEING DEAD,

23:15.698 --> 23:17.526
AND THEN YOU COLLECT
THE REWARD?

23:17.570 --> 23:20.050
THAT'S IT IN A NUTSHELL.SO, YOU AFTER MY REWARD?

23:20.094 --> 23:22.052
I'M NOT MAD AT YOU.
I JUST WANT TO KNOW.

23:22.096 --> 23:24.315
I'LL BE MAD AT YOU
IF YOU LIE TO ME, THOUGH.

23:24.359 --> 23:25.447
I DON'T WANT YOUR REWARD.

23:25.491 --> 23:27.275
I'LL BE SO MAD
IF YOU'RE LYING,

23:27.318 --> 23:28.798
YOU'LL HAVE ME
SCRATCHING THE DRAPES.I'M NOT LYING.

23:28.842 --> 23:31.192
PLEASE DON'T ATTACK
THE WINDOW TREATMENTS.

23:31.235 --> 23:33.412
OKAY.
GO BACK TO SLEEP.

24:30.077 --> 24:32.688
I'M A FRIEND OF NED'S.

24:34.560 --> 24:37.519
DOES HE TOUCH YOU?

24:37.563 --> 24:40.391
-SO, HOW WAS THE SERVICE?
-JUST PAID MY RESPECTS.

24:40.435 --> 24:42.916
YOU WEREN'T LOOKING
TO GETPAID?
HMM?

24:42.959 --> 24:44.526
MIGHT SEE A DEAD WOMAN
SPEAKING TO YOU IN CONFIDENCE

24:44.570 --> 24:47.007
AS AN OPPORTUNITY TO MAKE
A LOT OF MONEY BY YOUR LONESOME,

24:47.050 --> 24:49.400
REGARDLESS
OF PRIOR ARRANGEMENTS.

24:49.444 --> 24:51.228
THERE'S NO OPPORTUNITY
HERE.

24:51.272 --> 24:53.535
ARE YOU
THE BUSINESS PARTNER?YES, MA'AM.

24:53.579 --> 24:56.930
DOESN'T SHE LOOK A LOT
LIKE THAT DEAD GIRL?

24:56.973 --> 24:59.323
SHE LOOKS EXACTLY
LIKE THAT DEAD GIRL.

24:59.367 --> 25:01.282
TAKE THAT AS A COMPLIMENT.
SHE WAS PRETTY.

25:01.325 --> 25:02.936
PIE TIME.

25:02.979 --> 25:05.808
PIE TIME.

25:05.852 --> 25:08.115
I'VE BEEN RUMINATING --
AND BY RUMINATING,

25:08.158 --> 25:09.638
I MEAN PONDERING,
NOT CHEWING CUD.

25:09.682 --> 25:11.510
HOW ABOUT WE SOLVE MY MURDER
AND COLLECT THE REWARD?

25:11.553 --> 25:14.208
WOULDN'T THAT BE POETIC?
CERTAINLY AN ANECDOTE.

25:14.251 --> 25:16.079
SHE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
IN THE GROUND.

25:16.123 --> 25:17.559
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T WANT
THE REWARD.

25:17.603 --> 25:19.169
I WANTED YOU
NOT TO WANT THE REWARD.

25:19.213 --> 25:21.084
$50,000 --
THAT'S A LOT OF MONEY.

25:21.128 --> 25:24.174
THREE-WAY SPLIT --
30-30-40?

25:24.218 --> 25:26.133
IT'S ONLY FAIR I GET MORE.
I DID DIE FOR IT.

25:26.176 --> 25:28.222
I'M NOT A DETECTIVE.
I MAKE PIES.

25:28.265 --> 25:29.832
YOU CAN'T JUST TOUCH SOMEBODY'S
LIFE AND BE DONE WITH IT.

25:29.876 --> 25:31.138
YES, I CAN.
THAT'S HOW I ROLL.

25:31.181 --> 25:32.879
I COULD DO 30-30-40.

25:32.922 --> 25:34.620
SHE'S SUPPOSED TO BE DEAD.

25:34.663 --> 25:37.710
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE DEAD.
THIS IS PUSHING YOUR LUCK.

25:37.753 --> 25:40.234
YEAH.
WELL, LUCK PUSHED ME FIRST.

25:45.195 --> 25:46.588
IT'S JUST
SO SHOCKINGLY STUPID.

25:46.632 --> 25:48.198
I HAVE A HARD TIME
BELIEVING YOU DID IT.

25:48.242 --> 25:49.983
YOU JUST AGREED
TO BE HER PARTNER.

25:50.026 --> 25:52.115
OH, I INTEND TO PROFIT
FROM YOUR STUPIDITY.

25:52.159 --> 25:54.857
ARE YOU IN LOVE WITH HER?
IT'S THAT LEVEL OF STUPID.

25:54.901 --> 25:56.859
I'LL ADMIT TO BEING CONFUSED.
IT'S A VERY CONFUSING TIME.

25:56.903 --> 25:59.079
CHILDHOOD ISSUES,
DIGGING IN THE DIRT --

25:59.122 --> 26:00.384
IT'S ALL COMING UP.

26:00.428 --> 26:02.082
WE ALL HAVE
CHILDHOOD ISSUES, OKAY?

26:02.125 --> 26:04.258
BELIEVE ME, I GOT
THE FULL SUBSCRIPTION, OKAY?

26:04.301 --> 26:06.129
HORROR STORIES.

26:06.173 --> 26:07.783
I KIND OF KILLED HER DAD
WHEN I WAS 10.

26:07.827 --> 26:10.133
MAYBE NOT HORROR STORIES.

26:10.177 --> 26:12.701
SHE DOESN'T KNOW,
BUT I WANTED TO MAKE IT BETTER

26:12.745 --> 26:15.748
OR DIFFERENT THAN WHAT IT WAS
BECAUSE WHAT IT WAS HER DEAD,

26:15.791 --> 26:16.966
AND I DIDN'T WANT THAT
TO BE MY FAULT, TOO.

26:17.010 --> 26:19.273
WELL, WHO DIED INSTEAD?

26:20.622 --> 26:22.145
IT'S A RANDOM
PROXIMITY THING.

26:22.189 --> 26:26.062
-BITCH, I WAS IN PROXIMITY.
-I WASN'T THINKING.

26:26.106 --> 26:27.803
I WONDERED
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.

26:27.847 --> 26:29.675
HE WAS A VERY,
VERY BAD MAN.

26:29.718 --> 26:32.808
HE STOLE STUFF OFF DEAD PEOPLE
AND SOLD IT ON THE INTERNET.

26:32.852 --> 26:34.941
IT'S ALL IN THE OBITUARY.OH, THAT'S NICE.

26:34.984 --> 26:36.812
THE FACT THAT HE WAS
A VERY, VERY BAD MAN

26:36.856 --> 26:38.771
MAKES YOU FEEL BETTER
ABOUT WHAT YOU DID?

26:38.814 --> 26:40.642
YES. IMMENSELY.

26:40.686 --> 26:44.211
I WOULD HAVE FELT HORRIBLE
IF IT WAS YOU, FOR EXAMPLE.

26:44.254 --> 26:45.865
I'M NOT PROUD.

26:45.908 --> 26:47.431
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M GLAD YOU DID IT.

26:47.475 --> 26:49.651
IT MAKES THE WORST THING
I EVER DID SEEM INSIGNIFICANT.

26:49.695 --> 26:51.610
LISTEN TO YOU,
ALL JUDGY JUDGE.

26:51.653 --> 26:53.437
"JUDGY JUDGE"?

26:53.481 --> 26:55.439
LOOK, YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT THIS GIRL,

26:55.483 --> 26:57.441
EXCEPT SHE GOT HERSELF KILLED.

26:57.485 --> 26:59.879
[ CHUCK CLEARS THROAT ]

26:59.922 --> 27:02.011
I'M NOT WHO YOU THINK I AM.

27:02.055 --> 27:03.883
WHO DOES HE THINK
YOU ARE?

27:03.926 --> 27:06.233
THE SMALL-TOWN GIRL
WHO NEVER SAW THE WORLD,

27:06.276 --> 27:08.365
ONLY TO HAVE HER FIRST TIME OUT
BE HER LAST.

27:08.409 --> 27:10.150
WELL, THAT ISWHO I AM.

27:10.193 --> 27:13.414
BUT I WAS HOISTED
BY MY OWN PETARD.WHAT'S A PETARD?

27:13.457 --> 27:15.851
IN MY CASE, THE PETARD
IS THAT TAHITIAN GETAWAY.

27:15.895 --> 27:17.374
IT WAS A DEVIL'S BARGAIN.WHO'S THE DEVIL?

27:17.418 --> 27:18.941
DIDI DUFFIELD,

27:18.985 --> 27:20.639
MANAGER OF BOUTIQUE TRAVEL
TRAVEL BOUTIQUE.

27:20.682 --> 27:23.076
SHE OFFERED ME A HIGH-SEAS
ADVENTURE AT NO COST.

27:23.119 --> 27:24.643
ALL I HAD TO DO
WAS PICK UP A PACKAGE.

27:24.686 --> 27:29.996
-ARE YOU A DRUG MULE?
-NO. I'M A MONKEY MULE.

27:30.039 --> 27:32.825
Narrator: AND THESE ARE
THE MONKEYS IN QUESTION.

27:32.868 --> 27:35.175
YOU DIED FOR A PAIR
OF PLASTER MONKEYS.

27:35.218 --> 27:36.829
DIDI SAID
THEY WEREN'T WORTH MUCH.

27:36.872 --> 27:38.569
THEIR ONLY VALUE
WAS SENTIMENTAL.

27:38.613 --> 27:40.310
THOSE MUST HAVE BEEN
SOME EMOTIONAL MONKEYS.

27:40.354 --> 27:41.964
YOU SHOULD ASK DIDI
ABOUT ALL THIS.

27:42.008 --> 27:43.966
I'M VERY CURIOUS
AS TO WHAT SHE HAS TO SAY.

27:44.010 --> 27:46.665
Narrator: BOUTIQUE TRAVEL TRAVEL
BOUTIQUE MANAGER DIDI DUFFIELD

27:46.708 --> 27:48.841
HOPED THE $50,000 REWARD

27:48.884 --> 27:51.365
WOULD CATCH A KILLER
BEFORE A KILLER CAUGHT HER.

27:53.889 --> 27:57.197
THE REWARD FELL SHORT
OF ACHIEVING ITS DESIRED GOAL.

27:57.240 --> 27:59.895
OH.

27:59.939 --> 28:02.071
Chuck: I GUESS I CAN'T BE
TOO MAD AT HER.

28:02.115 --> 28:04.204
IS THAT HOW THEY FOUND ME?
IT'S HUMILIATING.

28:04.247 --> 28:05.945
I WONDER HOW LONG
SHE'S BEEN HERE.

28:05.988 --> 28:08.556
TOUCH THE POOR BITCH
AND ASK HER.

28:08.599 --> 28:11.124
ALRIGHT.

28:11.167 --> 28:13.996
I'M -- I'M SORT OF EMBARRASSED
TO DO IT IN FRONT OF YOU.

28:14.040 --> 28:15.998
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:17.870 --> 28:20.350
[ WATCH TICKING ]

28:25.094 --> 28:26.443
[ GASPS ]

28:26.487 --> 28:28.402
HEY, CHARLOTTE.

28:28.445 --> 28:29.925
HEY, DIDI.

28:29.969 --> 28:32.101
NOW, HOW'D I KNOW YOU'D BE
THE FIRST PERSON I'D SEE

28:32.145 --> 28:35.931
WHEN I GOT TO -- IS THIS --
WHICH ONE IS THIS?

28:35.975 --> 28:37.498
THIS IS NEITHER.

28:37.541 --> 28:39.326
WELL, MAYBE IT'S BOTH.
BUT, LISTEN, THIS IS THE DEAL.

28:39.369 --> 28:41.720
YOU GET TO TALK
FOR LIKE A MINUTE,

28:41.763 --> 28:43.765
WE'RE GONNA CATCH UP, AND THEN
YOU'RE NOT TALKING ANYMORE.

28:43.809 --> 28:45.549
DOES EVERYONE
GET TO DO THIS?

28:45.593 --> 28:46.768
'CAUSE, GIRL,
WE GOT TO BREAK IT DOWN.

28:46.812 --> 28:48.422
DID YOU KNOW
I WAS GONNA GET KILLED?

28:48.465 --> 28:50.467
I THOUGHT THERE MIGHT BE
THE POSSIBILITY, YES.

28:50.511 --> 28:53.122
I PROBABLY SHOULD HAVE
SAID SOMETHING.

28:53.166 --> 28:56.560
BUT TO BE HONEST, AND, REALLY,
WHY NOT AT THIS POINT?

28:56.604 --> 28:58.824
IF IT WAS SAFE,
I WOULD HAVE DONE IT MYSELF.

28:58.867 --> 29:02.044
GOD, THIS IS FANTASTIC.
BEING HONEST IS FUN.

29:02.088 --> 29:05.178
ASK HER WHO KILLED HER AND YOU
AND WHAT'S WITH THE MONKEYS.

29:05.221 --> 29:08.007
WHO ARE THOSE PEOPLE?THAT'S EMERSON.
I DON'T REALLY KNOW HIM.

29:08.050 --> 29:10.574
AND THIS IS NED.
HE WAS MY FIRST KISS.

29:12.489 --> 29:15.057
YOU'RE ADORABLE.
LOOK AT YOUR LI--

29:18.626 --> 29:21.237
YOU COULDN'T HAVE...
SCOOTED BACK A LITTLE?

29:21.281 --> 29:22.848
I DIDN'T KNOW SHE WAS
GONNA TOUCH MY CHEEK.

29:22.891 --> 29:25.807
WHO DOES THAT?ACTUALLY,
SHE DOES THAT A LOT.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.766
WHY WOULD
WHOEVER KILLED YOU

29:27.809 --> 29:29.419
KILL HER
WHEN HE GOT HIS MONKEYS?

29:29.463 --> 29:30.769
I DROPPED MY KEY
IN THE ICE MAKER.

29:30.812 --> 29:33.989
HE COULDN'T GET
INTO MY ROOM.

29:34.033 --> 29:36.122
OH, FOR PETE'S SAKE.

29:36.165 --> 29:38.167
THIS IS A NIGHTMARE.

29:38.211 --> 29:40.213
HE DOESN'T HAVE
THE MONKEYS.

29:40.256 --> 29:41.475
WHEN YOU GET MURDERED
ON A BOAT,

29:41.518 --> 29:43.216
WHERE DO THEY SEND
YOUR THINGS?

29:43.259 --> 29:45.871
YOUR NEXT OF KIN.

30:06.979 --> 30:08.763
YOU STAY HERE.

30:08.807 --> 30:10.417
I JUST WANT TO LOOK
IN THE WINDOW.

30:10.460 --> 30:12.767
YOU CAN HAVE YOUR PIE,
BUT YOU CAN'T EAT IT.

30:12.811 --> 30:14.203
Y'ALL ARE MAKING ME HUNGRY.

30:14.247 --> 30:15.988
I WAS SUPPOSED TO KEEP THEM
SANE, AND I LEFT.

30:16.031 --> 30:17.728
I'D JUST DIE IF ANYTHING
HAPPENED TO THEM --

30:17.772 --> 30:19.600
I MEAN I'D DIE AGAIN.

30:19.643 --> 30:21.297
WE'LL MAKE SURE
YOUR AUNTS ARE SAFE,

30:21.341 --> 30:23.169
AND THEN WE'LL CALL
THE POLICE.

30:23.212 --> 30:25.258
I WISH I COULD GIVE YOU
AN EMOTIONAL HEIMLICH

30:25.301 --> 30:27.129
SO YOU COULD COUGH UP THAT WAD
OF FEAR AND ANXIETY,

30:27.173 --> 30:29.915
BUT I CAN'T.

30:29.958 --> 30:32.352
I'D GIVE HER A HUG.

30:40.534 --> 30:42.884
THAT WAS FROM ME.

30:50.065 --> 30:52.676
Narrator: AUNT VIVIAN AND
AUNT LILY WERE ALL CHUCK HAD,

30:52.720 --> 30:55.549
AND BEFORE CHUCK,
ALL THEY HAD WERE EACH OTHER.

30:57.551 --> 31:00.423
WHILE STILL IN THEIR TEENS,
THEY MADE A NAME FOR THEMSELVES

31:00.467 --> 31:03.252
AS THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS.

31:11.086 --> 31:15.090
MANY, MANY, MANY YEARS LATER,

31:15.134 --> 31:19.312
STILL HOLDING ON TO THEIR FADING
GLORY AS UNDERWATER ARTISTES,

31:19.355 --> 31:21.923
THEIR LIVES WERE CHANGED FOREVER

31:21.967 --> 31:24.012
WHEN LILY,
WHILE CLEANING THE LITTER BOX,

31:24.056 --> 31:26.014
GOT DIRTY CAT SAND
IN HER EYE.

31:26.058 --> 31:27.233
OH, MY!

31:27.276 --> 31:29.104
NOT ONLY DID SHE LOSE HER EYE,

31:29.148 --> 31:32.716
BUT THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS
LOST THEIR CAREERS.

31:32.760 --> 31:34.849
THEY RETREATED BEHIND A FENCE

31:34.893 --> 31:38.722
AND MADE SURE THE WORLD
STAYED ON THE OTHER SIDE.

31:40.159 --> 31:42.422
-Vivian: HELLO?
-HI. MY NAME IS NED.

31:42.465 --> 31:44.598
I LIVED NEXT DOOR
20 YEARS AGO.

31:44.641 --> 31:47.731
I'M A --
WAS A FRIEND OF CHUCK'S.

31:47.775 --> 31:50.909
CHARLOTTE'S, RATHER.

31:50.952 --> 31:53.607
PLEASE, COME IN.

31:53.650 --> 31:55.348
PLEASE.

32:03.008 --> 32:05.010
CHARLOTTE WAS
A FIRECRACKER,

32:05.053 --> 32:06.707
ALWAYS TRYING TO GET US
OUT OF THE HOUSE,

32:06.750 --> 32:09.101
THREATENED TO BAKE
ANTIDEPRESSANTS INTO OUR FOOD.

32:09.144 --> 32:11.755
IT GOT TO THE POINT I WAS SCARED
TO EAT ANYTHING SHE COOKED.

32:11.799 --> 32:14.628
SHE WAS A GOOD COOK
AND A NICE GIRL.

32:14.671 --> 32:16.456
DO YOU LIKE GIRLS?

32:16.499 --> 32:18.066
YES, MA'AM.

32:18.110 --> 32:20.025
CHARLOTTE WAS
A NICE GIRL.

32:20.068 --> 32:21.243
WITH THE EXCEPTION
OF PUBERTY.

32:21.287 --> 32:22.897
WHICH WAS,
UNFORTUNATELY,

32:22.941 --> 32:24.551
WHEN LILY WAS GOING THROUGH
A CHANGE OF LIFE.

32:24.594 --> 32:27.858
IMPOLITE TO DISCUSS A PERSON'S
MENOPAUSE IN MIXED COMPANY.

32:27.902 --> 32:29.686
IT NEARLY KILLED ME.

32:29.730 --> 32:32.994
HORRIBLE THE WAY CHARLOTTE
DIED -- ON A CRUISE.

32:33.038 --> 32:36.476
LAST DAYS SPENT SURROUNDED
BY MIDDLE-AGED, OVERWEIGHT WOMEN

32:36.519 --> 32:39.261
WHO WEAR SWEATSHIRTS
WITH THINGS SEWN TO THEM.

32:39.305 --> 32:41.350
USUALLY KITTENS
MADE OF FELT.

32:41.394 --> 32:43.874
AND THE FOOD
IS PERFECTLY ATROCIOUS.

32:43.918 --> 32:46.312
UNLESS SHE ENJOYED
VOMITING AND DIARRHEA,

32:46.355 --> 32:48.531
I CAN'T IMAGINE SHE HAD
A GOOD LAST MEAL.

32:48.575 --> 32:50.272
A GOOD LAST MEAL
CAN GO A LONG WAY.

32:50.316 --> 32:52.013
OUR PENAL SYSTEM
MAKES A POINT OF IT.

32:52.057 --> 32:53.797
IT'S NICE SHE HAD
A LITTLE GLIMPSE OF THE WORLD

32:53.841 --> 32:55.495
BEFORE SHE DIED.

32:55.538 --> 32:57.149
EH, THE WORLD
ISN'T THAT GREAT.

32:57.192 --> 32:58.715
WELL, AT LEAST SHE HAD
THE GOOD SENSE NOT TO FLY.

32:58.759 --> 33:02.328
AIRPLANES FALL OUT OF THE SKY
EVERY DAY.

33:02.371 --> 33:04.112
[ SIGHS ]

33:07.246 --> 33:11.032
CHEESE? I WOULD RECOMMEND
THE PURE GOAT WITH BLUE ASH.

33:11.076 --> 33:13.208
IT HAS A GRASSY FLAVOR.

33:14.731 --> 33:16.342
IT DOES HAVE
A GRASSY FLAVOR.

33:16.385 --> 33:18.083
IT'S DELICIOUS
WITH CHARLOTTE'S HONEY.

33:18.126 --> 33:21.303
YOU HAVEN'T LIVED
UNTIL YOU'VE TASTED HER HONEY.

33:21.347 --> 33:23.610
THE HOMELESS LOVE IT.

33:25.003 --> 33:27.048
NOT TO CHANGE THE SUBJECT,

33:27.092 --> 33:30.008
BUT HAS THE CRUISE LINE
RETURNED HER BELONGINGS,

33:30.051 --> 33:32.401
SPECIFICALLY
A STAINLESS-STEEL BRIEFCASE?

33:35.187 --> 33:37.145
Narrator:
CHUCK COULDN'T REMEMBER

33:37.189 --> 33:40.061
WHY SHE WAS SO DESPERATE
TO LEAVE THIS LIFE BEHIND.

33:40.105 --> 33:42.716
SHE MISSED HER AUNTS.
SHE MISSED HER BEES.

33:44.109 --> 33:46.372
SHE MISSED EVERYTHING SHE WAS.

33:56.730 --> 33:59.037
[ SQUAWKS ]
HELLO!

34:09.221 --> 34:11.875
SMUGGLING MONKEYS
PUT AN END TO HER LIFE.

34:11.919 --> 34:13.703
CHUCK DIDN'T
WANT TO BE REMEMBERED

34:13.747 --> 34:15.792
AS THE LONELY TOURIST.

34:15.836 --> 34:18.926
SHE WANTED TO BE REMEMBERED
AS SOMETHING SWEETER.

34:50.218 --> 34:51.915
[ SQUAWKS ]

34:56.094 --> 34:58.270
Narrator:
UNAWARE OF LILY'S FATE UPSTAIRS,

34:58.313 --> 35:01.273
THE PIE MAKER DID HIS BEST
TO COMFORT VIVIAN.

35:01.316 --> 35:03.971
CHARLOTTE ALWAYS
WANTED TO GET AWAY.

35:04.014 --> 35:06.843
GOT AWAY FURTHER
THAN ANY OF US THOUGHT.

35:06.887 --> 35:09.150
IN A RARE MOMENT
OF SENSITIVITY,

35:09.194 --> 35:11.935
HE REACHED OUT
AND TOUCHED HER...

35:18.203 --> 35:19.769
[ SWALLOWS ]

35:19.813 --> 35:22.294
...NOT REALIZING
SHE DIDN'T LIKE BEING TOUCHED.

35:25.645 --> 35:28.126
I'LL GO SEE IF SHE NEEDS
ANY HELP BRINGING IT DOWN.

35:40.399 --> 35:42.749
AAH! AAH!

35:49.059 --> 35:50.800
DIDN'T I KILL YOU?

35:50.844 --> 35:54.021
[ GUN COCKS ]I CAN HOLD MY BREATH
FOR A LONG TIME.

36:03.465 --> 36:05.250
Narrator:
THE JIG APPEARED TO BE UP.

36:05.293 --> 36:07.600
AUNT LILY WAS LOOKING
DIRECTLY AT HER NIECE,

36:07.643 --> 36:10.516
HER NIECE WHO WASN'T
SUPPOSED TO BE ALIVE.

36:10.559 --> 36:13.736
AND IF SHE POSSESSED
TWO GOOD EYES,

36:13.780 --> 36:16.304
SHE WOULD HAVE SEEN HER.

36:26.706 --> 36:29.187
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:32.712 --> 36:35.715
Narrator: A RUSH OF WARMTH
WASHED OVER THE PIE MAKER.

36:37.543 --> 36:41.111
HE WOULD LATER DESCRIBE
THIS FEELING AS DELIGHT.

36:41.155 --> 36:44.724
THE GIRL HE RESCUED FROM DEATH
HAD RETURNED THE FAVOR.

36:53.080 --> 36:55.778
FORMER DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS
VIVIAN AND LILY CHARLES

36:55.822 --> 36:59.347
DEFEATED A DEADLY HOME INVADER
WHO MAY HAVE SOME CONNECTION

36:59.391 --> 37:01.436
WITH THE SMUGGLING-RELATED
MURDER OF THEIR NIECE,

37:01.480 --> 37:03.438
LONELY TOURIST
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

37:03.482 --> 37:05.962
WHEN ASKED ABOUT A DARLING
MERMAID DARLINGS REUNION,

37:06.006 --> 37:07.834
THE SISTERS MENTIONED
A BENEFIT PERFORMANCE

37:07.877 --> 37:09.575
TO SUPPORT
HONEY FOR THE HOMELESS

37:09.618 --> 37:11.620
WAS IN THE WORKS.

37:20.847 --> 37:25.330
WAS THIS REALLY AN ACT
OF KINDNESS -- ME HERE?

37:25.373 --> 37:27.462
WERE YOU REALLY TRYING
TO DO SOMETHING GOOD

37:27.506 --> 37:29.812
FOR NO OTHER REASON
THAN TO HELP ME?

37:29.856 --> 37:31.858
I WAS BEING SELFISH.

37:31.901 --> 37:34.252
I'D LOVE TO TELL MYSELF
I WAS BEING UNSELFISH,

37:34.295 --> 37:35.905
BUT I KNOW DEEP DOWN
IN MY PRIMAL SWEET SPOT,

37:35.949 --> 37:40.301
I WAS BEING UNSELFISH
FOR SELFISH REASONS.

37:40.345 --> 37:42.912
I JUST THOUGHT MY WORLD
WOULD BE A BETTER PLACE

37:42.956 --> 37:45.001
IF YOU WERE IN IT.

37:46.960 --> 37:49.267
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
I SHOULD KNOW?

37:51.181 --> 37:53.096
THE PIE MAKER
WANTED TO TELL CHUCK

37:53.140 --> 37:54.837
ABOUT THAT FATEFUL AFTERNOON

37:54.881 --> 37:57.405
WHEN HE INADVERTENTLY
KILLED HER FATHER.

37:57.449 --> 37:59.755
BUT INSTEAD, HE SAID...

38:00.930 --> 38:02.671
NO.

38:07.067 --> 38:08.677
WELL, I FIGURE
SINCE IT COST ME MY LIFE,

38:08.721 --> 38:10.810
I SHOULD GET TO KEEP
AT LEAST ONE.

38:10.853 --> 38:13.987
AND SEEING AS I WOULDN'T
BE ALIVE IF IT WEREN'T FOR YOU,

38:14.030 --> 38:16.424
I WANT YOU TO HAVE
THE OTHER ONE.

38:18.992 --> 38:21.168
IT'S LIKE THOSE LITTLE
HALF-HEART PENDANTS

38:21.211 --> 38:23.126
EXCEPT WITH MONKEYS.

38:27.087 --> 38:29.002
THANK YOU FOR BRINGING ME
BACK TO LIFE.

38:29.045 --> 38:30.786
YOU'RE WELCOME.

38:44.104 --> 38:46.933
OH! THESE ARE HEAVY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:56.377 --> 38:58.074
THE MONKEYS' VALUE

38:58.118 --> 39:00.381
WAS SIGNIFICANTLY MORE
THAN SENTIMENTAL.

39:00.425 --> 39:02.644
THEY WERE GOLDEN.

39:02.688 --> 39:06.735
THE MAN WHO KILLED CHUCK
WAS KILLED BY AUNT LILY.

39:06.779 --> 39:09.477
AFTER COLLECTING
THE $50,000 REWARD,

39:09.521 --> 39:11.871
VIVIAN AND LILY HAD
A RENEWED INTEREST

39:11.914 --> 39:13.960
IN THE WORLD ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THEIR FENCE.

39:14.003 --> 39:17.224
THEY RETREATED
FROM THEIR RETREAT...

39:17.267 --> 39:19.835
AND TOOK THE PLUNGE.

39:19.879 --> 39:23.143
EMERSON COD WAS PLUNGED INTO
SOMETHING ELSE ALTOGETHER --

39:23.186 --> 39:24.840
A THREE-WAY SPLIT.

39:24.884 --> 39:26.842
THIS WHOLE THING IS
SORT OF LIKE REINCARNATION

39:26.886 --> 39:28.931
BUT MORE IMMEDIATE.
SORT OF.

39:28.975 --> 39:30.498
DO YOU BELIEVE
IN REINCARNATION?

39:30.542 --> 39:33.240
HELL, NO.
THE PLANET'S FALLING APART.

39:33.283 --> 39:35.111
RIGHT NOW,
IT'S THE CHILDREN'S PROBLEM.

39:35.155 --> 39:37.549
WE REINCARNATE,
IT'S OURPROBLEM.

39:37.592 --> 39:38.680
AFTERNOON.

39:38.724 --> 39:40.421
YOU THE TOXICOLOGIST?

39:40.465 --> 39:42.554
YES.

39:42.597 --> 39:44.991
AREN'T YOU
THE DOG EXPERT?

39:46.296 --> 39:47.950
NO.

39:49.125 --> 39:51.214
UH-HUH.

39:51.258 --> 39:52.564
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

39:52.607 --> 39:56.611
ONE MATTHEW MILTENBERGER,

39:56.655 --> 40:00.049
37 YEARS, 6 HOURS,
AND 45 MINUTES OLD,

40:00.093 --> 40:02.269
WAS FOUND DEAD
IN THE LOBSTER TANK

40:02.312 --> 40:04.880
OF A FRANCHISE
STEAK AND LOBSTER HOUSE.

40:04.924 --> 40:06.447
BEFORE MR. MILTENBERGER

40:06.491 --> 40:08.928
COULD GET INTO THE SPECIFICS
OF HIS DEMISE...

40:11.104 --> 40:13.367
...CHUCK THOUGHT
IT WOULD BE NICE TO ASK...

40:13.411 --> 40:15.891
DO YOU HAVE ANY LAST WORDS
OR THOUGHTS OR REQUESTS?

40:19.199 --> 40:20.766
WHAT?

40:20.809 --> 40:22.768
JUST SOMETHING
I NEVER THOUGHT TO ASK.

40:24.857 --> 40:26.424
AS HE STARED AT HER,

40:26.467 --> 40:30.166
HE REACHED AROUND HIS BACK
AND HELD HIS OWN HAND,

40:30.210 --> 40:32.865
PRETENDING HE WAS HOLDING HERS.

40:32.908 --> 40:34.823
AND AT THAT VERY MOMENT,

40:34.867 --> 40:37.957
SHE WAS PRETENDING
TO BE HOLDING HIS.
